      "date": "2018-09-06 01:40:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDid you see https://review.whamcloud.com/32978 \"LU-11233 build: gcc8 support\"",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cdb1d60a076f552180a8efd090a5231d042927c3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 691,
        "name": "Dominique Martinet",
        "email": "asmadeus@codewreck.org",
        "username": "martinetd"
      },
      "date": "2018-09-06 08:42:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Did you see https://review.whamcloud.com/32978 \"LU-11233 build:\n > gcc8 support\"\n\nActually I hadn't, but this is a different subset -- the first two are (part) of some problem with old patchless that use the system's quota struct that was defined with MAXQUOTAS set to 2 yet use it with LUSTRE_MAXQUOTAS set to 3, overflowing the entry; I didn't find anything about that one (but honestly don't have the time to invest in a proper fix, I hacked the generated ldiskfs files on my machine)\n\n\nthe mgs_llog.c one is a false positive with gcc-7, it doesn't appear with gcc-8 so I'm not sure what to do with that one.\n\nI really didn't mean to push this, sorry for the noise :)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
  ],
